My "Unix" (ie Linux) TeX setup generates PDF which 
I view with Acrobat Reader, which
uses scaleable fonts. OK so far?

On the rare occasions I use dvi, I could view it with xdvi,
which asks the font renderer in X Windows to supply resources
from Type1 fonts. Thats "system support for scaleable fonts" in my
book (whether its good or bad is irrelevant).

